Yeah ?

32
00:01:28,014 --> 00:01:28,791
Hi, daddy.

33
00:01:29,978 --> 00:01:31,214
Hey, honey.

34
00:01:31,747 --> 00:01:32,621
What are you doing ?

35
00:01:34,040 --> 00:01:35,212
Feeding carlita.

36
00:01:35,535 --> 00:01:36,367
What are you doing ?

37
00:01:37,636 --> 00:01:39,022
Nothing. I, um...

38
00:01:41,002 --> 00:01:42,619
I'm just getting ready to go out back to work.

39
00:01:42,910 --> 00:01:44,881
Mommy and daddy Tom aren't home yet,

40
00:01:45,382 --> 00:01:47,251
and Kira and Jesse are making dinner.

41
00:01:47,714 --> 00:01:48,930
So I thought I'd ask you.

42
00:01:49,433 --> 00:01:50,587
Yeah, go ahead. Ask me what ?

43
00:01:52,528 --> 00:01:53,754
Are there monsters ?

44
00:02:01,903 --> 00:02:02,574
No.

45
00:02:05,259 --> 00:02:06,012
Are you sure ?

46
00:02:06,454 --> 00:02:08,126
'Cause you know those lights I saw in the sky

47
00:02:08,127 --> 00:02:11,121
during the hurricane, 
the ones that went into the water ?

48
00:02:11,122 --> 00:02:11,971
Yeah ?

49
00:02:13,107 --> 00:02:14,835
I thought they might be monsters.

50
00:02:16,755 --> 00:02:17,854
They weren't monsters, Rose.

51
00:02:17,855 --> 00:02:19,396
Then what were they ?

52
00:02:21,598 --> 00:02:24,220
How do you explain the unexplainable ?

53
00:02:25,315 --> 00:02:29,365
One family's devastated while 
another gets through this without a scratch.

54
00:02:29,705 --> 00:02:31,755
Hurricanes kind of havea mind of their own.

55
00:02:32,438 --> 00:02:34,242
We didn't ask to be hit this hard.

56
00:02:34,243 --> 00:02:35,876
Frankly, we didn't expect to be.

57
00:02:36,256 --> 00:02:38,755
But we're grateful the damage 
is nothing like what we saw

58
00:02:38,756 --> 00:02:40,628
with andrew back in '92.

59
00:02:41,201 --> 00:02:42,854
Uh, Mr. Mayor, we heard rumors of a quarantine.

60
00:02:42,855 --> 00:02:45,231
We're still working on all this.

61
00:02:49,385 --> 00:02:50,841
Aside from the damage to the hospital,

62
00:02:51,446 --> 00:02:54,655
we've received reports of chemical and fertilizer plants opening up

63
00:02:54,656 --> 00:02:56,774
as well as contaminants found in the water supply.

64
00:02:56,775 --> 00:02:59,277
Now when you consider that 
we still have hundreds of people missing--

65
00:02:59,278 --> 00:03:02,904
no one has authorized an actual quarantine yet--

66
00:03:02,905 --> 00:03:05,290
just a few checkpoints here and there.

67
00:03:06,438 --> 00:03:07,090
Russell ?

68
00:03:08,678 --> 00:03:09,386
Yeah, Dave ?

69
00:03:09,387 --> 00:03:10,933
Have you checked out that skeleton I found yet ?

70
00:03:10,934 --> 00:03:12,536
I'm on my way to do it right now.

71
00:03:13,943 --> 00:03:14,499
Oh, you moved it ?

72
00:03:14,500 --> 00:03:15,600
No, I took your car.

73
00:03:16,055 --> 00:03:16,942
Out into the hurricane slop.

74
00:03:16,943 --> 00:03:18,174
Dave, who cares ?

75
00:03:18,585 --> 00:03:19,907
I do, Russ.

76
00:03:19,908 --> 00:03:21,015
It's a collectible.

77
00:03:21,740 --> 00:03:22,452
Good-bye, Dave.

78
00:03:25,972 --> 00:03:27,427
Would you support a quarantine, doctor ?

79
00:03:29,579 --> 00:03:30,322
Doctor ?

80
00:03:34,292 --> 00:03:36,531
I was the one who originally suggested it.

81
00:03:37,035 --> 00:03:39,469
Sheriff, will your office be coordinating the relief effort--

82
00:03:39,470 --> 00:03:40,977
search and rescue, military ?

83
00:03:40,978 --> 00:03:42,786
Everyone will be working together on this,

84
00:03:42,787 --> 00:03:44,394
but my office will run point, yes.

85
00:03:44,395 --> 00:03:45,323
Over here.

86
00:03:45,927 --> 00:03:47,223
So you'll be in charge ?

87
00:03:47,626 --> 00:03:49,915
God's in charge. I just handle the paperwork. 
Yeah ?

88
00:03:50,611 --> 00:03:53,554
Sheriff, when can we expect to have 
electricity and running water again ?

89
00:03:53,956 --> 00:03:54,970
You'll be the first to know.

90
00:03:55,533 --> 00:03:57,252
Hey, your dad likes being on tv, doesn't he ?

91
00:03:58,187 --> 00:04:00,083
He always says, "presentation is everything."

92
00:04:01,793 --> 00:04:02,903
Rose, do you want some more juice ?

93
00:04:02,904 --> 00:04:04,032
No, thanks.

94
00:04:04,683 --> 00:04:05,405
Dr. Underlay,

95
00:04:05,727 --> 00:04:08,644
We understand that you went through 
quite an ordeal the night of the storm--

96
00:04:08,645 --> 00:04:10,318
13 hours in biscayne bay ?

97
00:04:11,265 --> 00:04:11,935
That's right.

98
00:04:12,239 --> 00:04:12,900
How are you feeling ?

99
00:04:13,184 --> 00:04:15,002
Under the circumstances, pretty fortunate.

100
00:04:15,335 --> 00:04:16,297
Rose, aren't you hungry ?

101
00:04:16,921 --> 00:04:17,844
I miss mommy.

102
00:04:20,152 --> 00:04:21,096
She's right there, rose.

103
00:04:22,273 --> 00:04:23,670
...operation center set up...

104
00:04:25,539 --> 00:04:27,447
No. She's not.

105
00:04:28,060 --> 00:04:29,540
Pretty scary night for you, too, sheriff.

106
00:04:29,541 --> 00:04:30,761
Your wife's very lucky.

107
00:04:32,341 --> 00:04:33,344
She's a survivor.

108
00:04:34,133 --> 00:04:35,006
Dr. Underlay ?

109
00:04:35,791 --> 00:04:38,624
- What is the extent of the damage in the hospital ?
- Larkin ! Larkin !

110
00:04:39,821 --> 00:04:41,697
Stay back behind the yellow tape.

111
00:04:43,629 --> 00:04:44,647
Dave, I'm working.

112
00:04:44,648 --> 00:04:47,309
This quarantine will kill us. 
We'll be completely cut off.

113
00:04:47,310 --> 00:04:48,724
It hasn't even happened yet, okay ?

114
00:04:48,725 --> 00:04:51,379
And even if it does, the hurricane relief groups  
will still have access, all right?

115
00:04:51,399 --> 00:04:52,816
The hurricane is not our problem.

116
00:04:53,709 --> 00:04:56,050
Dave, you're my brother--

117
00:04:56,634 --> 00:04:58,654
and I love you, but I am tired,

118
00:04:59,056 --> 00:05:00,497
I'm pregnant, and you're medicated.

119
00:05:00,498 --> 00:05:01,989
Will you please go back to your room ?

120
00:05:02,280 --> 00:05:02,596
No.

121
00:05:02,597 --> 00:05:05,050
Nurse, could you make sure he gets back to his room, please ?

122
00:05:05,051 --> 00:05:05,772
You suck.

123
00:05:05,773 --> 00:05:07,511
Russell will be here to pick you up in the morning.

124
00:05:07,512 --> 00:05:08,721
Fight the power, Larkin.

125
00:05:09,737 --> 00:05:10,933
Fight the power !

126
00:05:13,396 --> 00:05:17,319
.. major roads and some major highways will have their lanes reversed

127
00:05:17,320 --> 00:05:19,443
to handle the evacuation traffic.

128
00:05:19,885 --> 00:05:22,322
State officials hope to avoid a repeat of the mess

129
00:05:22,323 --> 00:05:25,342
that occurred with hurricane Floyd in 1999.

130
00:07:32,834 --> 00:07:33,919
- You know his name ?
- No

131
00:07:34,230 --> 00:07:36,030
- Any I.D. ?
- None that I could find.

132
00:07:36,101 --> 00:07:38,079
- What was he doing at your place ?
- I have no idea.

133
00:07:38,240 --> 00:07:39,900
Coming through ! Right over here.
Follow me. Come on.

134
00:07:40,220 --> 00:07:41,627
Our temp E.R.Is right over here.

135
00:07:43,608 --> 00:07:44,448
Coming through !

136
00:07:50,358 --> 00:07:51,321
One, two, three.

137
00:08:18,393 --> 00:08:19,778
How did this happen ?

138
00:08:47,562 --> 00:08:49,149
Hey, Russell ? 
Baby, you there ?

139
00:08:49,650 --> 00:08:50,148
Hey, honey.

140
00:08:50,149 --> 00:08:51,098
Where are you ?

141
00:08:51,377 --> 00:08:52,223
I'm at the hospital.

142
00:08:52,795 --> 00:08:53,658
Why ?

143
00:08:54,253 --> 00:08:56,354
I just found some guy in my station who was...

144
00:08:57,168 --> 00:08:58,217
who was cut up real bad.

145
00:08:58,218 --> 00:08:59,589
Who is he ? 
Is he gonna be okay ?

146
00:09:00,051 --> 00:09:00,662
I'm not sure.

147
00:09:01,157 --> 00:09:02,735
Listen, is the generator in the shed ?

148
00:09:04,158 --> 00:09:04,819
Don't...

149
00:09:05,875 --> 00:09:07,623
- Don't go to the shed.
- Why not ?

150
00:09:09,091 --> 00:09:11,240
Because it's dark down there.
I just don't want you by the water.

151
00:09:11,564 --> 00:09:13,764
It's dark in the house.
I need power. I need to work.

152
00:09:14,417 --> 00:09:15,889
Can you just grab a flashlight
and go in the bedroom ?

153
00:09:15,890 --> 00:09:17,270
I'll be home as soon as I can.

154
00:09:17,563 --> 00:09:19,239
Flashlight's not gonna run my computer.

155
00:09:19,395 --> 00:09:21,916
- Why do you need your computer ?
- Why are you being so weird ?

156
00:09:22,229 --> 00:09:24,339
No, no. I'm not being weird, 
I'm just being protective.

157
00:09:24,901 --> 00:09:26,512
Well, if you really want to be protective,

158
00:09:26,513 --> 00:09:28,649
don't introduce my brother to any more alligators.

159
00:09:29,493 --> 00:09:30,246
I gotta go, honey.

160
00:09:30,649 --> 00:09:32,307
She still thinks I was attacked by a gator ?

161
00:09:32,833 --> 00:09:34,531
- Let me see your leg, Dave.
- What for ?

162
00:09:34,532 --> 00:09:36,661
- Just let me see it.
- Ow ! All right.

163
00:09:39,366 --> 00:09:40,089
Okay, easy.

164
00:09:41,426 --> 00:09:43,999
- Why haven't you told Larkin the truth yet ?
- I don't know what the truth is.

165
00:09:44,279 --> 00:09:48,479
Yes--yes, you do.
I was attacked by an E.B.E--

166
00:09:49,344 --> 00:09:52,148
- an extraterrestrial biological entity.
- We don't know that.

167
00:09:52,880 --> 00:09:55,658
Oh, okay. I was sucked under water by a bright,

168
00:09:55,659 --> 00:09:57,976
orange sea blob and had my flesh branded.

169
00:09:58,127 --> 00:09:59,453
Yeah, that's more plausible,right ?

170
00:10:06,798 --> 00:10:07,421
What ?

171
00:10:12,859 --> 00:10:13,791
What, Russ ?

172
00:10:15,773 --> 00:10:16,515
Let me see that.

173
00:10:20,364 --> 00:10:21,015
Oh, man.

174
00:10:23,589 --> 00:10:24,156
Who is this ?

175
00:10:24,157 --> 00:10:25,774
It's a guy I found in my station today.

176
00:10:25,775 --> 00:10:28,548
This guy has the exact same wounds as me.  
He's been prodded.

177
00:10:28,549 --> 00:10:30,964
This is definitely the work of an E.B.E., Russ.

178
00:10:31,096 --> 00:10:33,873
- I could show you hundreds--
- I can show you hundreds of pictures of weird fish

179
00:10:33,874 --> 00:10:35,195
being tossed up by a tsunami.

180
00:10:35,222 --> 00:10:38,372
- It's not a f--
- Just because something's unfamiliar doesn't mean it's an alien.

181
00:10:38,744 --> 00:10:42,110
Okay. So it was a fish that I found 
wrapped around that skeleton ?

182
00:10:43,245 --> 00:10:45,718
Were those just fins shooting through the guy's skull and rib cage ?

183
00:10:47,135 --> 00:10:47,890
Taken the time to study that ?

184
00:10:47,891 --> 00:10:51,196
I was going to, till I got a little way laid by a man bleeding to death.

185
00:10:55,348 --> 00:10:56,236
What's a guy in a wet suit doing

186
00:10:56,237 --> 00:10:58,096
swimming around the everglades in the middle of a hurricane ?

187
00:10:58,097 --> 00:10:58,892
I don't know.

188
00:11:00,161 --> 00:11:02,833
You'd better find out before 
someone else decides to take a little dip.

189
00:12:10,879 --> 00:12:11,885
You did really great out there.

190
00:12:13,100 --> 00:12:13,728
No, I didn't.

191
00:12:13,729 --> 00:12:16,729
I mean, I'm trying, but I really...

192
00:12:17,100 --> 00:12:18,517
Whoa, whoa, whoa.
Come here. Come here.

193
00:12:19,905 --> 00:12:22,665
After what you've been through ? 
You did great.

194
00:12:26,927 --> 00:12:27,509
What's up ?

195
00:12:32,967 --> 00:12:35,126
I think I lost my wedding ring in the storm.

196
00:12:37,419 --> 00:12:38,816
I've looked everywhere for it.

197
00:12:41,225 --> 00:12:42,100
We didn't lose you.

198
00:13:01,106 --> 00:13:01,789
Hey, Russell ?

199
00:13:04,403 --> 00:13:05,325
Hey, Russell ?

200
00:13:06,914 --> 00:13:07,597
Yeah, Dave ?

201
00:13:07,800 --> 00:13:10,079
Hey. So what did you find out ?

202
00:13:10,154 --> 00:13:12,022
- I haven't checked the skeleton yet.
- Why not ?

203
00:13:12,747 --> 00:13:14,048
I'm trying to figure outwhat happened to the guy.

204
00:13:14,049 --> 00:13:15,649
You know what happened to the guy.

205
00:13:16,073 --> 00:13:18,178
He was attacked like me, like the skeleton.

206
00:13:18,179 --> 00:13:19,624
Why are you in such denial here ?

207
00:13:19,757 --> 00:13:21,177
Dave, you need to give me some time.

208
00:13:21,178 --> 00:13:22,901
Yeah, while the mother ship is landing ?

209
00:13:23,565 --> 00:13:24,524
Will you please just hurry up

210
00:13:24,525 --> 00:13:25,774
and take a look at the damn thing ?

211
00:13:26,196 --> 00:13:28,366
And try not to scratch my car.

212
00:14:26,534 --> 00:14:28,031
We're gonna turn off the generator now.

213
00:14:29,047 --> 00:14:31,447
And you got your flashlight and your water.

214
00:14:32,733 --> 00:14:34,447
And we're gonna be right in the next room, okay ?

215
00:14:34,448 --> 00:14:36,030
Why hasn't mommy called ?

216
00:14:36,883 --> 00:14:38,250
Well, the phones are out, Rose.

217
00:14:39,134 --> 00:14:40,863
She could call on the radio.

218
00:14:41,577 --> 00:14:44,405
Even when she works late, 
she always calls.

219
00:14:44,406 --> 00:14:46,308
Yeah, I know. But it's different tonight.

220
00:14:47,184 --> 00:14:48,725
Hurricanes make everything different.

221
00:14:48,726 --> 00:14:50,811
I don't want things to be different.

222
00:14:53,625 --> 00:14:54,369
Okay.

223
00:14:57,252 --> 00:14:58,006
Hey, Kira ?

224
00:14:58,468 --> 00:14:59,221
Okay.

225
00:15:02,256 --> 00:15:02,929
Night, Rose.

226
00:15:05,553 --> 00:15:06,923
Are you allergic to any medication ?

227
00:15:06,924 --> 00:15:08,616
No.

228
00:15:12,215 --> 00:15:12,907
Deep breath.

229
00:15:15,678 --> 00:15:19,737
The nurse told me that I was in the water all night.
Is that true?

230
00:15:20,662 --> 00:15:21,736
That's what I understand.

231
00:15:22,441 --> 00:15:23,254
And again.

232
00:15:25,677 --> 00:15:28,239
I hear you had a similar experience.

233
00:15:29,587 --> 00:15:30,278
Yeah.

234
00:15:31,565 --> 00:15:33,704
Guess we both must be pretty good swimmers, huh ?

235
00:15:34,631 --> 00:15:36,016
Oh, well, that's just it--

236
00:15:37,503 --> 00:15:38,798
I don't know how to swim.

237
00:15:43,764 --> 00:15:45,953
Come on, bring it through !

238
00:15:47,049 --> 00:15:47,537
All right.

239
00:15:47,538 --> 00:15:49,983
Don't pitch that too close to the landing zone, boys !

240
00:15:50,356 --> 00:15:52,048
We don't want the choppers giving us haircuts.

241
00:15:52,049 --> 00:15:54,048
Sheriff,we've got U.S. 1 cleared,

242
00:15:54,049 --> 00:15:55,847
and we're almost done with Krome avenue.

243
00:15:55,848 --> 00:15:57,804
Good job, Lewis. Turnpike still closed ?

244
00:15:57,805 --> 00:15:58,566
Yes, sir.

245
00:15:58,567 --> 00:15:59,440
Keep it that way.

246
00:16:00,555 --> 00:16:01,513
5-mile radius !

247
00:16:01,514 --> 00:16:02,153
Tom ?

248
00:16:02,958 --> 00:16:05,383
Hey, Russ. What brings you out of the jungle at this hour ?

249
00:16:05,384 --> 00:16:07,178
Did you authorize the military to enter the park ?

250
00:16:07,913 --> 00:16:08,674
Why would I do that ?

251
00:16:09,198 --> 00:16:10,788
A military vehicle passed by my place tonight,

252
00:16:10,789 --> 00:16:12,973
and I just found a guy out there that was pretty messed up--

253
00:16:13,276 --> 00:16:14,606
Air Force. I found his dog tags.

254
00:16:14,607 --> 00:16:15,944
I don't control the military, Russ.

255
00:16:15,945 --> 00:16:16,505
Yeah, I know.

256
00:16:16,506 --> 00:16:18,451
But you are working with them now, aren't you ?

257
00:16:20,351 --> 00:16:21,475
The guy's name was Paxton.

258
00:16:21,788 --> 00:16:23,032
He was in a wet suit when I found him.

259
00:16:24,753 --> 00:16:26,511
- He was in a wet suit ?
- Yeah.

260
00:16:28,663 --> 00:16:30,109
- Did he say anything ?
- He was unconscious.

261
00:16:31,818 --> 00:16:33,777
Do you have any idea why he might have been out there ?

262
00:16:34,723 --> 00:16:35,385
