00:34:45,393 --> 00:34:46,005
I love you.

528
00:34:46,650 --> 00:34:48,006
I love you, too, daddy.

529
00:34:59,201 --> 00:34:59,773
Reed.

530
00:35:00,205 --> 00:35:01,201
Did you get in touch with Val ?

531
00:35:01,202 --> 00:35:03,826
Yeah, I ran your story by her.
She wants to talk to you.

532
00:35:04,287 --> 00:35:04,920
Great.

533
00:35:06,891 --> 00:35:07,422
Val.

534
00:35:08,588 --> 00:35:09,363
Larkin.

535
00:35:11,132 --> 00:35:12,667
Reed told you about this missing airman ?

536
00:35:13,674 --> 00:35:15,818
Val, his wife didn't even know he was down here.

537
00:35:15,819 --> 00:35:18,386
It sounds to me like the military is covering something up.

538
00:35:19,169 --> 00:35:20,895
She thought he was ona mission overseas.

539
00:35:22,285 --> 00:35:23,796
I-I told her that he was here in the hospital

540
00:35:23,797 --> 00:35:26,006
and I offered to bring her down here,

541
00:35:26,007 --> 00:35:28,534
but she seemed so scared.

542
00:35:30,685 --> 00:35:31,599
Larkin, the man is dead.

543
00:35:32,503 --> 00:35:32,910
What ?

544
00:35:32,911 --> 00:35:34,413
I just talked to the hospital.

545
00:35:36,111 --> 00:35:37,560
That's not the story I want to tell.

546
00:35:37,561 --> 00:35:41,646
I-I want our viewers to see how we're coping, adapting.

547
00:35:42,150 --> 00:35:43,078
How did you get out of town ?

548
00:35:43,079 --> 00:35:44,485
I thought there were roadblocks.

549
00:35:44,486 --> 00:35:45,947
I went around them.

550
00:35:46,481 --> 00:35:47,529
You could've been arrested.

551
00:35:47,530 --> 00:35:49,434
Since when do you care how I get a story ?

552
00:35:50,199 --> 00:35:50,897
Val ?

553
00:35:53,715 --> 00:35:55,920
This man was obviously down here 
on some kind of classified mission.

554
00:35:55,921 --> 00:35:57,587
Now he's dead, and no one's talking about it.

555
00:35:57,588 --> 00:36:00,046
And you're concerned about my driving record ?

556
00:36:01,091 --> 00:36:02,428
I don't want this story, Larkin.

557
00:36:03,061 --> 00:36:04,236
Not this story.

558
00:36:17,539 --> 00:36:18,110
Dave !

559
00:36:18,995 --> 00:36:19,547
What ?

560
00:36:20,514 --> 00:36:21,306
Paxton's dead.

561
00:36:23,106 --> 00:36:24,718
- Give me your keys.
- What ? Why ?

562
00:36:24,719 --> 00:36:26,632
Just give me your keys.

563
00:36:28,623 --> 00:36:29,491
Uh... how do you know he's dead ?

564
00:36:29,492 --> 00:36:30,712
Larkin just called.

565
00:36:31,335 --> 00:36:33,716
She said Paxton's wife knew nothing 
about him being down here.

566
00:36:34,400 --> 00:36:37,132
And apparently the Air Force just swooped in 
and took his body away.

567
00:36:39,262 --> 00:36:40,669
Well, then how do you know he's dead ?

568
00:36:41,313 --> 00:36:43,653
I mean, did anybody actually see him dead, Russ ?

569
00:36:47,564 --> 00:36:48,060
Call me crazy...

570
00:36:48,061 --> 00:36:49,662
I don't care if you're crazy, Dave.

571
00:36:53,078 --> 00:36:55,409
I care about how all this affects my family.

572
00:36:57,340 --> 00:36:58,686
If there's something going on here,

573
00:36:59,178 --> 00:37:00,603
something bigger than the hurricane...

574
00:37:04,686 --> 00:37:06,876
how can I protect my kids 
when they're not with me ?

575
00:37:07,801 --> 00:37:08,806
They're with you, Russ.

576
00:37:10,111 --> 00:37:10,895
They're in the town.

577
00:37:12,150 --> 00:37:13,893
But right now the town may need your protection

578
00:37:13,894 --> 00:37:14,933
just as much as they do.

579
00:37:28,118 --> 00:37:28,820
What are you looking for ?

580
00:37:29,263 --> 00:37:31,056
Hair, nails, teeth--

581
00:37:31,057 --> 00:37:33,151
anything to pull some D.N.A. from.

582
00:37:34,067 --> 00:37:34,759
Okay.

583
00:37:45,360 --> 00:37:46,034
Is this yours ?

584
00:37:49,419 --> 00:37:50,111
No.

585
00:37:54,473 --> 00:37:55,438
"Two become one."

586
00:37:56,614 --> 00:37:57,447
That's the inscription.

587
00:37:58,161 --> 00:37:58,734
What ?

588
00:38:02,021 --> 00:38:03,187
Any idea who this belongs to ?

589
00:38:13,706 --> 00:38:14,660
Will you marry me ?

590
00:38:16,912 --> 00:38:17,956
Why'd you do this ?

591
00:38:22,801 --> 00:38:23,782
'Cause you're my wife.

592
00:38:31,221 --> 00:38:32,044
How's it fit ?

593
00:38:35,099 --> 00:38:36,023
Pretty good.

594
00:38:38,104 --> 00:38:38,901
Where'd you get it ?

595
00:38:38,902 --> 00:38:40,414
Stole it off a looter.

596
00:38:45,339 --> 00:38:45,990
Mommy.

597
00:38:48,684 --> 00:38:50,069
Mommy, I'm ready for bed.

598
00:38:50,754 --> 00:38:51,969
I'll be right there, honey.

599
00:38:56,182 --> 00:38:56,782
Hi.

600
00:38:59,472 --> 00:39:00,959
- You brush your teeth ?
- Yep.

601
00:39:03,533 --> 00:39:05,390
- You want Mobat ?
- Yeah.

602
00:39:13,811 --> 00:39:18,243
- I'm sorry I didn't call you last night, honey.
- It's okay.

603
00:39:18,976 --> 00:39:20,462
No, it's not.

604
00:39:24,754 --> 00:39:25,747
I want you to know

605
00:39:26,533 --> 00:39:29,898
I'm gonna try very hard not to let that 
happen ever again, okay?

606
00:39:31,688 --> 00:39:33,354
I was just kinda worried.

607
00:39:34,632 --> 00:39:35,466
I know.

608
00:39:37,586 --> 00:39:38,560
And you know what ?

609
00:39:40,962 --> 00:39:42,106
You're not gonna lose me.

610
00:39:43,615 --> 00:39:46,237
Ever. I promise.

611
00:39:48,970 --> 00:39:50,387
Even when you die ?

612
00:39:53,122 --> 00:39:55,698
Well, you know, that's not gonna happen

613
00:39:55,699 --> 00:39:59,682
for a very, very, very long time.

614
00:40:03,560 --> 00:40:05,980
I've been wanting to tell you something, mommy.

615
00:40:07,137 --> 00:40:07,829
Hey, Mare.

616
00:40:09,229 --> 00:40:10,010
It's the hospital.

617
00:40:16,855 --> 00:40:18,070
Can you save it till tomorrow ?

618
00:40:26,268 --> 00:40:28,085
- Good night, sweetheart.
- Night, mommy.

619
00:40:28,800 --> 00:40:30,668
- I love you.
- I love you, too.

620
00:40:42,095 --> 00:40:43,218
This is dr. Underlay.

621
00:40:47,239 --> 00:40:50,001
- You feelin' okay now, Rosie ?
- I guess.

622
00:40:51,499 --> 00:40:52,212
Hey...

623
00:40:54,213 --> 00:40:55,899
is there somethin' you wanna tell me ?

624
00:40:59,958 --> 00:41:02,248
- Okay.
- Okay.

625
00:41:11,775 --> 00:41:15,090
During the hurricane, I saw lots of lights.

626
00:41:15,742 --> 00:41:16,758
They were beautiful.

627
00:41:17,804 --> 00:41:21,430
They fell out of the sky and into the water.

628
00:41:22,907 --> 00:41:24,033
And then...

629
00:41:25,812 --> 00:41:27,087
they swam away.

630
00:41:39,870 --> 00:41:41,587
Can you keep a secret, honey ?

631
00:41:46,945 --> 00:41:49,063
I saw them, too.

